# Consistency Rules for HeroPortfolio

## Constants — never hardcode inline

All limits, prices, and user-facing copy strings live in **`src/lib/constants.ts`**.

When editing any of these files, import from constants instead of using literal values:

- `src/lib/db/portfolio.ts` — uses `FREE_AI_USES_PER_MONTH`
- `src/app/api/summarize-link/route.ts` — uses `FREE_AI_EXHAUSTED_MESSAGE`
- `src/components/PortfolioContentEditor.tsx` — uses `FREE_AI_LABEL`
- `src/components/PricingPlansClient.tsx` — uses `PRICES`, `FREE_AI_LABEL`, `FAMILY_PLAN_MAILTO`

**If you change a limit or price, update `src/lib/constants.ts` first, then verify no raw values remain.**

## Back navigation button

The "← Timeline" back button is **`<BackToTimeline />`** from `src/components/BackToTimeline.tsx`.

Do NOT inline the pill-button JSX. Pages that use it:
- `src/app/timeline/album/page.tsx`
- `src/app/timeline/analytics/page.tsx`
- `src/app/timeline/badges/page.tsx`
- `src/app/pricing/page.tsx`

## General rule

If a UI pattern or string appears in 2+ places and you need to change it, extract it first, then change in one place.
